  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protecting communities&#x2019; land and natural resources</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project, a partnership between CAFOD and Namati, builds on previous pilots for protecting community land and natural resources alongside empowering communities, especially women and youth, in decision-making and governance of land.
The project will collect data and other related information that will inform the government on the development of strategies and guidelines for implementing the Customary Land Rights and National Land Commission Bills when they are passed into law.
The project will contributes:
- To educate communities on tenure rights and the related laws and policies
- To help communities develop rules and governance structures to govern their land and natural resources 
- To build the capacity of communities to participate in the mapping of their land 
- To map and document family and community land in the project communities
- To empower and prepare communities to deal with large-scale land acquisitions</narrative>
  </description>
